      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualifications documented at gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Simulation performed by a PhD-level biofluid dynamics engineer with five years of CFD experience in cardiovascular device applications. Formal use-error analysis not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection documented at gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for rotating blood pump flows. Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) applied. Model form justification documented in simulation report; formal uncertainty analysis not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; nominal input values documented at gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Fluid properties (density 1056 kg/m3, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s), hemolysis model constants, and geometric dimensions documented from published sources. Sensitivity analysis not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; experimental sample description documented at gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark dataset uses a single manufactured pump specimen. Sample-to-sample variability characterization not required at MRL 2. Pump geometry confirmed via coordinate measurement machine to within ±0.05 mm of nominal CAD."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; parameter equivalency between validation and COU noted at gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "Validation and COU share identical geometry and fluid properties. The only difference is the use of whole blood rheology in the COU versus Newtonian analog in validation; this is noted as a model assumption and accepted at MRL 2 without formal equivalency analysis."
    }
